Switching between classes and coding sessions, or trying out other applications, isn't always easy.

(Especially when your teachers think you're not concentrating when your brain is literally multitasking.)

For this example,
I'm offering a linear TI-89 script that will reset the configuration settings.
This is a (roughly) factory configuration,
( Safer than manually via the Memory Menu )

You can easily change every settîngs to your own. As you develop your own applications, your script will become almost unnecessary. 

I hope you'll find useful to insert `customkil()` somewhere between your own settings.
